OL,3,CBlood victim's daughter criticises
OL,4,Cappointment of new advisor on
OL,5,Ccompensation
OL,7,FFamilies who have been waiting decades
OL,8,Ffor compensation after falling victim
OL,9,Fto the contaminated blood scandal say
OL,10,Fthe government's choice to chair a
OL,11,Fgroup advising on compensation could
OL,12,Flead to more suffering.
OL,14,FThousands of patients were infected
OL,15,Fwith HIV and hepatitis C through
OL,16,Fcontaminated blood products in the
OL,17,F1970s and 80s.
